{{see|ancien régime}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From {{F.}} ''Ancient Régime'', ''Old Rule'', ''Old Order''; the word first appeared in English in print in 1794.

===Proper noun===
'''[[Ancien]] [[Régime]]''' (''no plural form'')

# {{cattag|historically pejorative connotations}} The aristocratic social and political system established in France under the [[Valois]] and [[Bourbon]] dynasties, overthrown by the [[w:French Revolution|French Revolution]] of 1789.

